            1）	Keep calm and quiet and your wrist should be close against to the bottom of iband’ s screen. Do not swing your arm when measuring.
2）	Nonstandard wearing manners influence HR measurement like iband not exactly close against your wrist, arm swinging or iband moving on skin a little. Moreover, tighter wearing, lifted-up arm and clenched fist have bad impact on blood circulation, which can lead to failure on HR measurement. The proper ways to measure your HR are to keep your arm flat and keep yourself relaxed and calm and keep your wrist close against the iband. However, although you wear the iband in the proper ways, HR measurement can be failed by the influence of individual difference like scars on skin.





